HEADWORD: Fallopian
<hw>Fal*lo"pi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Fallopius</ets>, or <ets>Fallopio</ets>, a physician of Modena, who
died in 1562.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
discovered by, Fallopius; <as>as, the <ex>Fallopian</ex> tubes or
oviducts, the ducts or canals which conduct the ova from the ovaries to
the uterus</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

